WEBVTT

00:24.260 --> 00:27.060
CHAPTER VII.

00:27.900 --> 00:35.300
For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the Most High God, who met Abraham,

00:35.720 --> 00:42.980
returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him, to whom also Abraham gave a tenth

00:42.980 --> 00:52.880
part of all, first being by interpretation king of righteousness, and after that also king of Salem,

00:52.880 --> 01:00.880
which is king of peace, without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning

01:00.880 --> 01:09.560
of days nor end of life, but made like unto the Son of God, abideth a priest continually.

01:10.220 --> 01:18.760
Now consider how great this man was, unto whom even the patriarch Abraham gave the tenth of the

01:19.360 --> 01:27.580
And verily, they that are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a

01:27.580 --> 01:36.860
commandment, to take tithes of the people according to the law, that is, of their brethren, though they

01:36.860 --> 01:45.320
come out of the loins of Abraham, but he whose descent is not counted from them, received tithes

01:45.320 --> 01:54.540
of Abraham, and blessed him that had the promises, and without all contradiction, the less is blessed

01:54.540 --> 02:04.200
of the better. And here men that die receive tithes, but there he receiveth them, of whom it is

02:04.200 --> 02:17.360
that he liveth, and as I may so say, Levi also who receiveth tithes, paid tithes in Abraham, for he was

02:17.360 --> 02:25.100
yet in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met him. If therefore perfection were by the

02:25.100 --> 02:32.420
Levitical priesthood, for under it the people received the law, what further need was there that

02:32.420 --> 02:39.740
another priest should rise after the order of Melchizedek, and not be called after the order of Aaron?

02:40.060 --> 02:49.160
For the priesthood being changed, there is made of necessity a change also of the law, for he of whom these

02:49.160 --> 02:58.480
things are spoken pertaineth to another tribe, of which no man gave attendance at the altar, for it is

02:58.480 --> 03:06.640
evident that our Lord sprang out of Judah, of which tribe Moses spake nothing concerning priesthood.

03:06.940 --> 03:16.580
And it is yet far more evident, for that after the similitude of Melchizedek, there ariseth another priest,

03:17.120 --> 03:24.480
who is made not after the law of a carnal commandment, but after the power of an endless life.

03:25.090 --> 03:34.880
For he testifieth, thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek, for there is verily a

03:34.880 --> 03:41.800
disannulling of the commandment going before, for the weakness and unprofitableness thereof,

03:42.080 --> 03:50.060
for the law made nothing perfect, but the bringing in of a better hope did by the

03:50.060 --> 04:00.500
law, which we draw nigh unto God. And inasmuch as not without an oath, he was made priest, for those

04:00.500 --> 04:10.160
priests were made without an oath, but this with an oath by him that said unto him, The Lord swear

04:10.160 --> 04:18.620
and will not repent, thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek. By so much was

04:18.620 --> 04:27.200
made a surety of a better testament, and they truly were many priests, because they were not

04:27.200 --> 04:35.660
suffered to continue by reason of death. But this man, because he continueth ever, hath an

04:35.660 --> 04:44.260
unchangeable priesthood, wherefore he is able also to save them to the uttermost that come unto God

04:44.260 --> 04:52.980
by him, seeing he ever liveth to make intercession for them. For such an high priest became us,

04:52.980 --> 05:01.280
who is holy, harmless, undefiled, separate from sinners, and made higher than the heavens,

05:02.320 --> 05:09.080
who needeth not daily as those high priests to offer up sacrifice, first for his own sins,

05:09.080 --> 05:17.480
and then for the people's. For this he did once, when he offered up himself. For the law maketh

05:17.480 --> 05:25.020
men high priests which have infirmity, but the word of the oath which was since the law maketh

05:25.020 --> 05:34.960
the son who is consecrated forevermore. Chapter 8. Now, of the things which we have spoken,

05:34.960 --> 05:42.860
this is the sum. We have such an high priest, who is set on the right hand of the throne of

05:42.860 --> 05:51.120
the majesty in the heavens, a minister of the sanctuary, and of the true tabernacle which the

05:51.120 --> 05:59.040
Lord pitched, and not man. For every high priest is ordained to offer gifts and sacrifices, wherefore

05:59.040 --> 06:08.620
it is of necessity that this man have somewhat also to offer. For if he were on earth, he should

06:08.620 --> 06:16.020
not be a priest, seeing that there are priests that offer gifts according to the law, who serve

06:16.020 --> 06:23.400
unto the example and shadow of heavenly things, as Moses was admonished of God when he was about

06:23.400 --> 06:31.440
to make the tabernacle. For see, saith he, that thou make all things according to the pattern

06:31.440 --> 06:40.460
shewed to thee in the mount. But now hath he obtained a more excellent ministry, by how much

06:40.460 --> 06:50.100
also he is the mediator of a better covenant, which was established upon better promises. For

06:50.100 --> 06:56.520
if that first covenant had been faultless, then should no place have been sought for the second.

06:57.180 --> 07:03.680
For finding fault with them, he said, Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, when I will make

07:03.680 --> 07:10.620
a new covenant with the house of Israel, and with the house of Judah. Not according to the covenant

07:10.620 --> 07:17.460
that I made with their fathers, in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land

07:17.460 --> 07:26.100
of Egypt, because they continued not in my covenant, and I regarded them not, saith the Lord. For this is

07:26.100 --> 07:32.420
the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel, after those days, saith the Lord. I will

07:32.420 --> 07:39.800
put my laws into their mind, and write them in their hearts, and I will be to them a God, and they

07:39.800 --> 07:48.080
shall be to me a people. And they shall not teach every man his neighbor, and every man his brother,

07:48.400 --> 07:55.760
saying, Know the Lord, for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest. For I will be merciful

07:55.760 --> 08:04.200
to their unrighteousness, and their sins and their iniquities will I remember no more. In that he

08:04.970 --> 08:14.340
covenant he hath made the first old, now that which decayeth and waxeth old is ready to vanish away.

08:15.460 --> 08:25.160
Chapter 9. Then verily, the first covenant had also ordinances of divine service, and a worldly

08:25.160 --> 08:32.520
sanctuary. For there was a tabernacle made, the first wherein was the candlestick, and the table,

08:32.520 --> 08:40.200
and the showbread, which is called the sanctuary. And after the second veil, the tabernacle,

08:40.540 --> 08:47.920
which is called the holiest of all, which had the golden censer, and the ark of the covenant,

08:48.400 --> 08:56.400
overlaid round about with gold, wherein was the golden pot that had manna, and Aaron's rod that

08:56.400 --> 09:05.740
it, and the tables of the covenant. And over it the cherubims of glory, shadowing the mercy seat

09:05.740 --> 09:13.220
of which we cannot now speak particularly. Now, when these things were thus ordained,

09:13.560 --> 09:21.230
the priest went always into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the service of God. But into the

09:21.230 --> 09:28.150
second went the high priest alone, once every year, not without blood, which he offered for

09:28.150 --> 09:36.210
himself, and for the errors of the people. The Holy Ghost this signifying that the way into the

09:36.210 --> 09:45.690
holiest of all was not yet made manifest, while as the first tabernacle was yet standing. Which was

09:45.690 --> 09:53.510
a figure for the time then present, in which were offered both gifts and sacrifices, that could not

09:53.510 --> 10:01.630
make him that did the service perfect. As pertaining to the conscience, which stood only in meats and

10:01.630 --> 10:09.670
drinks and divers washings, and carnal ordinances imposed on them until the time of reformation.

10:09.670 --> 10:17.190
But Christ, being come in high priest of good things to come, by a greater and more perfect

10:17.190 --> 10:24.910
tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this building, neither by the blood of goats

10:24.910 --> 10:33.550
and calves, but by his own blood, he entered in once into the Holy Place, having obtained

10:33.550 --> 10:43.110
eternal redemption for us. For if the blood of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of in heifer

10:43.110 --> 10:50.990
sprinkling the unclean sanctified to the purifying of the flesh, how much more shall the blood of

10:50.990 --> 10:58.710
Christ, who through the eternal spirit offered himself without spot to God, purge your conscience

10:58.710 --> 11:07.590
from dead works to serve the living God. And for this cause, he is the mediator of the New Testament,

11:08.050 --> 11:13.870
that by means of death, for the redemption of the transgressions that were under the first

11:13.870 --> 11:28.690
testament, they which are called might receive the promise of eternal inheritance. For where a

11:28.690 --> 11:37.730
death of the testator, for a testament is a force after men are dead, otherwise it is of no strength,

11:38.270 --> 11:45.610
at all, while the testator liveth, whereupon neither the first testament was dedicated with

11:45.610 --> 11:52.790
our blood. For when Moses had spoken every precept to all the people, according to the law, he took

11:52.790 --> 12:01.310
the blood of calves and of goats with water and scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book

12:01.310 --> 12:09.910
and all the people, saying, This is the blood of the testament which God hath enjoined unto you.

12:10.450 --> 12:17.190
Moreover, he sprinkled with blood both the tabernacle and all the vessels of the ministry,

12:17.190 --> 12:25.630
and almost all things are by the law purged with blood, and without shedding of blood

12:25.630 --> 12:35.010
there is no remission. It was therefore necessary that the patterns of things in the heavens should

12:35.010 --> 12:42.470
be purified with these, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.

12:42.470 --> 12:50.130
For Christ is not entered into the holy places made with hands, which are the figures of the true,

12:50.430 --> 12:58.690
but into heaven itself now to appear in the presence of God for us. Nor yet that he should

12:58.690 --> 13:06.130
offer himself often, as the high priest entereth into the holy place every year with blood of

13:06.130 --> 13:13.370
others. For then must he often have suffered since the foundation of the world, but now once

13:13.370 --> 13:20.990
in the end of the world hath he appeared to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself.

13:21.530 --> 13:32.010
And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment. So Christ was once offered

13:32.010 --> 13:39.670
to bear the sins of many, and unto them that look for him shall he appear the second time without

13:39.670 --> 13:49.490
sin unto salvation. End of chapters seven through nine. Recording by Simon Wainwright.

